I need to correct one technical point from my previous answer: UBI containers cannot be registered normally with subscription-manager; Red Hat disables registration while it is running in container mode. The files below accomplish the result you actually need by permanently including a version-specific Satellite repository configuration and entitlement certificate bundle. Downstream Dockerfiles can immediately run yum install or dnf install without registering again.  

Red Hat normally recommends supplying the repository configuration and entitlement keys as build secrets rather than putting them in the published image. Because you specifically need reusable internal builder images, keep this project and its container registry tightly restricted.  

