7. README.md

# Image Builder
Builds internal UBI init images with persistent access to the Lockheed Martin
Red Hat Satellite repositories.
## Images
- `ubi7-init-satellite`
- `ubi8-init-satellite`
- `ubi9-init-satellite`
- `ubi10-init-satellite`
## Tags
Main-branch builds publish:
- `latest`
- `sha-<commit>`
- `pipeline-<pipeline-number>`
Feature-branch builds additionally publish:
- `<branch-name>`
## Important security restriction
These images contain Satellite entitlement certificate material.
The GitLab project, container registry, and all child images must remain private
and restricted to approved internal users and systems.
Do not push these images to an external registry.
## Creating the RHSM bundles
Run the bundle-generation script on a registered RHEL system matching each
major version:
```bash
sudo ./scripts/create-satellite-bundle.sh 7
sudo ./scripts/create-satellite-bundle.sh 8
sudo ./scripts/create-satellite-bundle.sh 9
sudo ./scripts/create-satellite-bundle.sh 10

This creates:

rhsm-ubi7.tar.gz
rhsm-ubi8.tar.gz
rhsm-ubi9.tar.gz
rhsm-ubi10.tar.gz

Upload the four archives under:

Settings
→ CI/CD
→ Secure Files

The archives must never be committed to Git.

## One-time setup after pasting the files
On one real RHEL system for each major release, install the Katello consumer RPM and register it using the activation key you found. Give the four Satellite hosts recognizable names such as:
```text
lit-image-builder-rhel7
lit-image-builder-rhel8
lit-image-builder-rhel9
lit-image-builder-rhel10

After verifying the correct repositories are enabled, run:

sudo ./scripts/create-satellite-bundle.sh 7

Repeat on 8, 9, and 10.

Upload the resulting four .tar.gz files under:

image-builder
→ Settings
→ CI/CD
→ Secure Files
→ Upload File

GitLab Secure Files supports binary files up to 5 MB, stores them outside the repository, and makes them available to CI jobs.  

Then add these CI/CD variables:

RHSM_UBI7_SECURE_FILE_ID
RHSM_UBI8_SECURE_FILE_ID
RHSM_UBI9_SECURE_FILE_ID
RHSM_UBI10_SECURE_FILE_ID

Each value is the numeric GitLab Secure File ID for its corresponding archive.

Also verify these existing variables:

RELEASE_TOKEN
CA_CERT

CA_CERT should remain a File variable.

Once those are present, commit the files to create-builder-images. Your existing merge request will stop saying “contains no changes,” and the pipeline should create four parallel build jobs.

One limitation remains: the embedded entitlement certificate can eventually be revoked or expire. Normal image rebuilds will not require registration, but the corresponding Secure File bundle must be replaced when Satellite rotates that credential. There is no reliable way to make a copied Satellite entitlement credential valid forever.